   </sense>
   <sense group="1" n="2" name="Approach someone else with an unpleasent issue, usu. to criticize" type="">
      <commentary>
       Syntax Is:
        NP1[actor] CONFRONT NP2[actor] (PP NP3)
         NOTE: does not imply that either NP is hostile or that a
        confrontation will take place. 
      </commentary>
      <examples>
      I'm going to have to confront Lucas about stealing my dollar.
      We confronted him with the evidence.
      He confronted her with his complaints.
      </examples>
