   </sense>
   <sense group="1" n="3" name="deal with something unpleasent head on" type="">
      <commentary>
        Syntax Includes:
        NP1[agent] CONFRONT NP2[topic[abstract]]
        NOTE: One argument is always abstract. This is a metaphorical usage
        of sense 1. 
      </commentary>
      <examples>
        We had never been confronted by such beauty.
        Jara was confronted by complex moral decisions.
        This is a problem most people hardly expect to confront.
      </examples>
